opardy! and regular Jeopardy! During Celebrity Jeopardy! anyone could get all the answers; there’s an accessibility that makes you feel like you’re smart. I think Leno’s jokes are similar in that way. Real Jeopardy! requires an attempt at greater mind function.</p><p><a href='http://www.playboy.com/playground/view/playboy-interview-jimmy-kimmel'>Playboy Interview: Jimmy Kimmel</a>.</p></blockquote><p>That&#8217;s an excellent way of putting it, don&#8217;t you think? I prefer Letterman to Leno in part because Dave forces me to pay attention. If I&#8217;m reading email and only half-listening, I might miss out on a crucial line that explains why he got another big laugh three jokes later.</p>
